\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 2.           Nothofagus}             Blume
\par  

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By J.R. Akeroyd.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Deciduous or evergreen trees. Buds fusiform. Flowers anemophilous. Male flowers axillary, solitary or in 2- or 3-flowered clusters, sessile or subsessile; perianth campanulate; stamens 8-40. Female flowers usually 3 in each 4-partite cupule; styles 3, short. Nuts (1-)3, mostly triquetrous.
\par

\par

