\pard\f0\fs28 Deciduous trees or shrubs. Buds ovoid. Flowers entomophilous, scented, in erect catkins, male in the upper, female in the lower part of the same catkin. Male flowers with 6-partite perianth; stamens 10-20. Female flowers usually 3 in each cupule; ovary 6-locular; styles 7-9. Nuts large, brown, coriaceous, 1-3 together in a spiny cupule which dehisces irregularly by 2-4 valves.
